body:
The following code:

      class test_class;
          integer a;

          function integer f();
              test_class t1;
              t1 = new this;
              return t1.a + 1;
          endfunction
      endclass

Generates the error:

    %Error: new_this.sv:9:18: New-as-copier passed different data type 'CLASSREFDTYPE 'test_class'' then expected 'CLASSREFDTYPE 'test_class''
                        : ... note: In instance 'test'
    9 |         t1 = new this;
      |                  ^~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)

Which doesn't make sense as the passed data type is the same as expected. The code also works in other sims.

Note that the problem can be worked around with a temporary:

          function integer f();
              test_class t1, t2;
              t2 = this;
              t1 = new t2;

> What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

verilator --binary test.sv

[test.tar.gz](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/19547310/test.tar.gz)

> What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?

Verilator 5.035 devel rev v5.034-93-ged1e3ec4a

> What OS and distribution are you using?

WSL2 / Ubuntu 24
